Description: A free and open-source connection manager (fork of Asbrú CM)
 Ásbrú Plus is a community-maintained fork of Ásbrú Connection Manager.
 It provides a graphical interface for organizing and automating remote
 terminal sessions over SSH, RDP, VNC, Telnet and SFTP.
 .
 Key features:
  - Tabbed terminal sessions with cluster support
  - Expect-based login automation
  - KeePass and KeePassXC integration
  - Port forwarding and SOCKS5 proxy support
  - Session logging and scripting
 .
 This fork targets Ubuntu 24.04 LTS and newer Debian-based systems,
 includes security fixes and FreeRDP3 support.
